DataType.Name: In
DataType.Comment: Value to or from Analog Unit X

DataType.Name: Out_Min
DataType.Comment: Unit Value at lowest level Ymin

DataType.Name: Out_Max
DataType.Comment: Unit Value at highest level Ymax

DataType.Name: Out_REAL
DataType.Comment: Scaled value in Units Y as REAL

DataType.Name: Out_percent1
DataType.Comment: Scaled value in 0-100% X as 0 to 100%

DataType.Name: Out_percent2
DataType.Comment: Scaled value in -100% to +100% X as -100% to 100%

DataType.Name: Extrapolate
DataType.Comment: Output value not limited by Out_Max/Out_Min

DataType.Name: Group
DataType.Comment: Set to 1-99 if this alarm belongs to a group

DataType.Name: Delay
DataType.Comment: Delay before the alarm goes on

DataType.Name: ErrorID
DataType.Comment: Any Error code can be stored here

DataType.Name: AnalogInput
DataType.Comment: The analog input for limit comparison

DataType.Name: DigitalInput
DataType.Comment: The digital input for level detection

DataType.Name: Disabled
DataType.Comment: Set ON to disable the alarm

DataType.Name: ACK
DataType.Comment: Acknowledge the alarm with this bit

DataType.Name: Reset_Counter
DataType.Comment: Reset alarm counter with this bit

DataType.Name: ActiveNoACK
DataType.Comment: Input is in alarm state but not ACKed

DataType.Name: NormalNoACK
DataType.Comment: Input is normal but not ACKed

DataType.Name: ActiveAndACK
DataType.Comment: Input is in alarm state and ACKed

DataType.Name: GroupDigital_Alarm
DataType.Comment: There is a digital alarm in specified group

DataType.Name: Alarmstate_Digital
DataType.Comment: Digital input is on after Delay and Not Disabled

DataType.Name: Alarmstate_AnalogL1
DataType.Comment: Analog input is on after Delay and Not Disabled

DataType.Name: Alarmstate_AnalogL2
DataType.Comment: Analog input is on after Delay and Not Disabled

DataType.Name: Digital_True
DataType.Comment: Digital is on and not Disabled

DataType.Name: ACKed
DataType.Comment: Ackowledge signal from table or Input
